<br>
i completed my robe part of the quest some time ago, but being that the Robe of the Whistling fist is a very nice robe to have, like any other monk. i waited till the VERY end of the quest to turn it in.<br>
for the Book of the celestial fist part.<br>
<br>
need to camp the Rast of Guk in Lguk.<br>
personally spent 20+ hours there.<br>
need Targin from Sol B.<br>
then you need a red sash and purple headband.<br>
i bought these at 1kpp.<br>
some other stuff that is easily tailored and combined to make your first robe<br>
now for the 2nd robe.<br>
this is easy. you just need your first robe and the Pipe off the rare spawn in Karnors and Chardok.<br>
now you need to turn them in to a mob in DL.<br>
now you have a kick ass robe.<br>
<br>
next part is you need a book from Skyfire. the book of immortals.<br>
take that to erude and you get a note.<br>
the note + your new kick ass robe turned in to the Kaiaren in Trakanons teeth will get you the celestial fist book<br>
<br>
now for the mob part of the quest.<br>
<br>
there are 4 seperate fights involved witht he monk epic.<br>
<br>
Eejag ( Lavastorm )<br>
Gwan (Plane Of Sky)<br>
Trunt ( Nurga )<br>
Deep, Vorash, and Xenvorash. ( LOIO )<br>
<br>
each one of these fights involves between 12 to 30 people.<br>
<br>
imagine the time involved to get the people together for each of these fights. not to mention i paid for the port stones to POS and the peridots for the clerics.<br>
now think of time for the people who helped me. <br>
<br>
after all that, turn in the final items and be kicked off the server and lose the fang and not have your epic. i still had the book tho, not sure why.<br>
<br>
now spend the next 5 days sending numerous emails and petitions to be called a liar and that there is nothign they can do. <br>
no roll backs<br>
no reimbursement of the fang<br>
cant even notice that their logs are WRONG !<br>
ask if i can give up the celestial fist book and get my robe back. no !  because there is no records of me ever having the robe of the whistling fist ! even tho i had the book in my inventory when talking to Zinric. and if you llok at the top of this post you will see i needed the robe at some point in time.<br>
even tho i included a complete list of the names of the people who helped me saturday night, ther eis still no proof i ever had the fang to turn in.<br>
<br>
now on top of that, have a Guide threaten to disband you guild if they petitioned to help you.<br>
<br>
you would start to be pissed off at some point in this wouldnt you?<br>
